Shouldn't you be at the hospital,
looking after a certain other soldier?

02:43.043 --> 02:46.274
Is there any way you can find it
in your heart to forgive me?

02:48.348 --> 02:51.181
I wonder if these two get together.

02:54.488 --> 02:57.821
I'll forgive you on one condition.

02:57.891 --> 03:02.294
- What's that?
- Dance with me.

03:28.755 --> 03:30.746
Explain one thing to me.

03:32.125 --> 03:38.325
What kind of desperate and pathetic
emotional cripple

03:38.398 --> 03:40.923
would actually buy that as an ending?

03:47.407 --> 03:50.535
Rosie, do you think that in real life

03:50.610 --> 03:54.046
Tad Hamilton is the man
he seems to be on the screen?

03:54.114 --> 03:58.813
Absolutely. I mean,
you just can't fake that kind of thing.

04:00.520 --> 04:04.115
What do you think Tad Hamilton
is doing right now?

04:05.859 --> 04:07.486
I'll bet he's in church.

04:13.867 --> 04:14.856
[Tad] Watch this.

04:17.971 --> 04:20.098
[Tad] Yeah! Whoo!

04:25.979 --> 04:28.345
- Told you that was him, right?
- Yeah.

04:28.415 --> 04:29.313
Tad Hamilton.

04:29.382 --> 04:32.010
[Driven Levy]
You don't make it easy on us, Tad.

04:32.085 --> 04:33.382
[Tad] What do you mean?

04:33.453 --> 04:35.444
This is the shot the paparazzi got.

04:37.791 --> 04:41.352
Congratulations. You're actually
drinking, driving, smoking,

04:41.428 --> 04:43.726
leering and groping at the same time.

04:43.797 --> 04:48.825
Which, on the one hand, is just about
the coolest thing I've ever seen.

04:48.902 --> 04:49.960
Richard.

04:50.036 --> 04:55.201
But, on the other hand, it can be argued
this might be bad for the image.

04:55.275 --> 04:57.436
You play characters who have heart.

04:57.510 --> 05:00.343
This is a person
who will have a heart attack.

05:00.413 --> 05:04.679
I can't believe you guys are blaming
my unemployment on this photograph.

05:04.751 --> 05:09.017
You are not unemployed.
Dockworkers are unemployed.

05:09.089 --> 05:12.490
You are simply between
million-dollar paydays.

05:12.559 --> 05:18.327
As are we, since we both get
a percentage of your payday.

05:19.532 --> 05:21.523
But this isn't about us.

05:21.601 --> 05:26.629
Whatever happened to that part in the
Jimmy Ing movie? I'm perfect for that.

05:26.706 --> 05:29.607
Well, he's taking a breath.

05:30.710 --> 05:33.577
- He's what?
- He's taking a breath.

05:33.647 --> 05:35.706
He's pausing before deciding.

05:35.782 --> 05:38.216
He's hemming and hawing
and taking a breath.

05:38.284 --> 05:41.378
And this is only going
to make him breathe more.

05:41.454 --> 05:45.220
- What do we do?
- Asphyxiate the son of a bitch.

05:45.291 --> 05:48.818
- We generate a little positive PR.
- What are you, an interpreter?

05:48.895 --> 05:53.559
I'm saying we just need
to do something, Tad,

05:53.633 --> 05:57.296
to remind Jimmy Ing and America
that you are the boy next door.

05:57.370 --> 05:59.429
I am the boy next door,

05:59.506 --> 06:03.704
if you happen to live
in a very dysfunctional neighborhood.

06:43.283 --> 06:49.119
[Pete] Congratulations. You've eaten
your body weight in Pringles.

06:49.189 --> 06:51.180
What's your favorite Pringle?

06:51.257 --> 06:53.817
Sour cream and onion or original?

06:53.893 --> 06:58.193
Well, the sour cream and onion
has a very strong taste.

06:58.264 --> 07:01.825
So if you're eating a small amount,
half a can, you want that strength.

07:01.901 --> 07:06.065
But if you're eating more, you want
the original. It's a cleaner flavor.

07:06.139 --> 07:11.133
Wait until you discover barbecue flavor.
You'll finally become a woman.

07:11.211 --> 07:14.339
How's Modern Grocer
treating you over there, Pete?

07:14.414 --> 07:16.905
This is the swimsuit issue.

07:22.555 --> 07:25.922
- oh, my God.
- What is it?

07:25.992 --> 07:28.586
- Win a date with Tad Hamilton.
- What?

07:28.661 --> 07:30.925
It's to benefit Save the Children.

07:30.997 --> 07:34.262
- That is so like him.
- Saving children. I know.

07:34.334 --> 07:35.767
Ohhh!

07:38.138 --> 07:41.232
- Should I enter?
- Why not?

07:41.307 --> 07:44.037
Sure. Heaven is just a mouse click away.

07:45.478 --> 07:47.810
A mouse click and 1 00-buck donation.

07:47.881 --> 07:50.213
We can raise 1 00 bucks.

07:54.487 --> 07:58.617
- With your permission, Petey.
- I'm sorry?

08:01.661 --> 08:03.629
- Paper or plastic?
- Paper, please.

08:03.696 --> 08:08.497
Would you help Rosalee win a date with
Tad Hamilton and help Save the Children?

08:08.568 --> 08:10.502
I certainly would.

08:15.842 --> 08:18.936
- Aren't these great?
- The best.

08:19.012 --> 08:21.537
Along with a $1 25 check

08:21.614 --> 08:26.210
in recognition of yet another Piggly
Wiggly Store Manager of the Month Award.

08:26.286 --> 08:29.153
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, Mr. Ruddy.

08:29.222 --> 08:31.690
So, Pete, when do we
lose you to Richmond?

08:31.758 --> 08:34.283
Because you're running
out of wall space here.

08:35.761 --> 08:39.198
Well, I got my acceptance letter
to Virginia State.

08:39.265 --> 08:42.428
- That's good.
- And I got my student loan.

08:42.501 --> 08:46.598
So, there's just one more thing.

08:46.673 --> 08:49.904
- What?
- There's someone here that I...

08:52.278 --> 08:54.269
I need to have a discussion with

08:54.347 --> 08:58.010
about the going
to Richmond with me issue.

09:01.354 --> 09:03.515
Jars are full.

09:04.557 --> 09:07.458
I love everybody in this store so much.

09:07.527 --> 09:10.690
Sorry for interrupting. Sorry.

09:28.481 --> 09:30.711
It was nice to meet you.

09:30.783 --> 09:32.842
It was nice to meet you, too.

09:32.919 --> 09:35.251
- Good night.
- Good night.

09:39.993 --> 09:41.483
- Are you taking off?
- Yes, sir.

09:41.561 --> 09:43.153
Muchas gracias.

09:43.229 --> 09:45.697
Hasta el próximo miércoles.

09:46.900 --> 09:50.233
I am the Albanian one, Mr. Hamilton.

09:50.303 --> 09:53.431
I'm sorry.
Could you tell the other one...

09:53.506 --> 09:57.033
"Muchas gracias" and
"hasta el próximo miércoles."

09:57.110 --> 09:59.101
- Will do.
- Thank you.

11:15.188 --> 11:17.383
oK, what do I need to beat you?

11:18.858 --> 11:22.089
Double 1 4, or it's all over.

11:22.161 --> 11:24.652
That's not going to be a problem.

11:26.332 --> 11:30.928
Don't miss. Don't miss, don't miss,
don't miss, don't miss, don't miss.

11:31.004 --> 11:33.802
Um, are you actually doing that? Yeah.

11:44.450 --> 11:49.114
And now Pete will get
the bartendress's attention.

11:49.188 --> 11:53.386
- She's waiting for you.
- And we're waiting for our round, Pete.

11:54.494 --> 11:56.485
Fine.

11:58.564 --> 11:59.929
Angelica.

12:06.506 --> 12:10.772
Yes, Pete?
What is the object of your desire?

12:14.080 --> 12:16.275
We need another round.

12:17.517 --> 12:20.748
one day, Pete, one day,

12:20.820 --> 12:24.551
I know that the answer to that question
will be "You, Angelica."

12:24.624 --> 12:28.151
"You are the object of my desire."

12:29.562 --> 12:33.760
oK. But for now
we'll just go with the beers.

12:43.042 --> 12:45.411
oh, Pete.

12:45.451 --> 12:47.402
Enough. Thank you, ladies.

12:47.480 --> 12:49.971
You don't like her
the teeniest, tiniest bit?

12:50.049 --> 12:52.040
What? Rosie...

12:52.118 --> 12:54.882
No, she's not my type, oK?

12:54.954 --> 12:57.650
[Rosie] You are so particular.

12:57.723 --> 12:59.714
Who the heck are they?

13:00.726 --> 13:03.388
If that fire alarm went off again...

13:03.463 --> 13:06.091
[Pete] Why would they send
a news crew for that?

13:06.165 --> 13:07.928
Wait a second.

13:15.208 --> 13:17.199
Right here, please.

13:22.515 --> 13:27.009
In first class you get a DVD player
and may view the film of your choice.

13:27.086 --> 13:30.021
I'd like to touch intimately
whoever thought of that.

13:30.089 --> 13:33.718
[announcer] We would like to begin
boarding our first-class passengers.

13:33.793 --> 13:36.421
- That's you.
- I know.

13:36.496 --> 13:38.623
Guys. Just take it easy, oK?

13:38.698 --> 13:42.259
Just give me a hug and tell me
to have a good time, please?

13:42.335 --> 13:43.768
oK.

13:47.106 --> 13:50.837
Just be careful, oK?

13:51.511 --> 13:54.912
- What do you mean?
- I mean that this guy is Tad Hamilton.

13:54.981 --> 13:59.748
In his life, he's probably
slept with like 1 5, 20 women.

14:00.987 --> 14:03.854
No way. That's not even
physically possible.

14:03.923 --> 14:07.086
Besides, like he's going
to be interested in me.

14:07.160 --> 14:12.757
If he claims he doesn't like watching
sports, he's trying to sleep with you.

14:12.832 --> 14:14.163
Got it.

14:14.233 --> 14:17.464
If he claims to love animals,
he's trying to sleep with you.

14:17.537 --> 14:20.335
- ok.
- Guys are guys. Rich or poor.

14:20.406 --> 14:23.466
Famous or grocers.

14:23.543 --> 14:26.603
- Right.
- Just do me one favor, ok?

14:28.814 --> 14:31.180
- Guard your carnal treasure.
- ok.

14:31.250 --> 14:34.378
- Just guard your carnal treasure.
- Thanks, Pete.

14:34.453 --> 14:36.648
- Remember everything.
- I will.

14:36.722 --> 14:39.156
- Remember how he smells.
- I will.

14:39.225 --> 14:42.194
But not just vaguely.
I want good, solid similes.

14:42.261 --> 14:47.790
For example: he smells like a forest
on the first day of spring.

14:47.867 --> 14:51.462
oK, Cathy.
You're going to miss your flight.

14:51.537 --> 14:54.165
- I will bring you similes.
- Thank you.

14:55.241 --> 14:58.142
I almost forgot. I got you something.

14:58.211 --> 15:00.975
It's regular flavor.

15:01.981 --> 15:05.849
In case you don't like
the prime rib in first class.

15:06.619 --> 15:08.951
Thank you, Pete.

15:12.391 --> 15:14.382
Right this way.

15:17.763 --> 15:21.358
- Just guard your carnal treasure.
- I heard you.

15:56.636 --> 15:59.605
- That's me.
- Welcome to Los Angeles.

17:05.003 --> 17:06.800
Oh!

17:07.440 --> 17:10.500
- Can I have these?
- No.

17:10.576 --> 17:12.874
Do you want to think about it?

17:12.944 --> 17:14.970
Gee, what...

17:15.047 --> 17:17.880
Tell me why you're making me
have dinner with an okie.

17:17.950 --> 17:21.317
Because she's wholesome
as the amber waves of grain.

17:21.387 --> 17:24.185
And she's not an okie.
She's from West Virginia.

17:25.156 --> 17:27.147
So sorry.

17:27.760 --> 17:30.354
You never wear them.
Can I just have them?

17:31.697 --> 17:35.098
- So what's her name anyway?
- Rosalee Futch.

17:35.167 --> 17:37.328
Sounds insanely hot.

17:37.403 --> 17:40.065
It's very nice to meet you, Tad.

17:41.474 --> 17:44.136
It's so nice to meet you, Tad.

17:45.177 --> 17:47.975
It's great to meet you.

17:48.047 --> 17:50.038
Please, just follow the rules.

17:50.116 --> 17:53.051
"Smile for the cameras.
No brown liquor or cigarettes."

17:53.119 --> 17:55.110
- Fine.
- Very good.

17:55.187 --> 17:57.678
What about Jimmy Ing?
Have we heard anything?

17:57.757 --> 17:59.588
No. Still breathing.

17:59.658 --> 18:02.491
I passed Ashton Kutcher in my car
and he seemed happy.

18:02.561 --> 18:06.827
He's happy for other reasons. I'm sorry.
We have not heard from Jimmy Ing.

18:06.899 --> 18:09.595
Hey, guys, how's this in the shoulders?

18:10.736 --> 18:11.815
Seriously.
Because I got some yoga stuff.

18:16.455 --> 18:19.578
Your films will stand the test of time.

18:23.322 --> 18:26.689
Your films will stand the test of time.

18:37.770 --> 18:40.830
Hi. I'm Tad.

18:43.209 --> 18:47.270
Your standing films will time
and test themselves.

18:49.448 --> 18:52.611
Thank you. You're pretty.

18:53.819 --> 18:56.913
It's Roseanne, right?
I'm sorry, what is it?

18:58.891 --> 19:01.416
Ricky?

19:01.494 --> 19:03.860
- It's Rosalee.
- Rosalee.

19:03.929 --> 19:06.727
Rosalee. Nice to meet you.

19:08.401 --> 19:12.667
- So, you ready? ok, let's...

19:17.243 --> 19:19.234
Yikes-a-bee.

19:21.113 --> 19:23.946
So, how was your flight?

19:24.016 --> 19:26.678
Your films will stand the test of time.

19:28.788 --> 19:30.119
Thank you.

19:31.290 --> 19:33.758
- So, you ready?
- For what?

19:33.826 --> 19:35.817
Right this way.

19:52.511 --> 19:54.376
Rosalee Futch.

20:05.624 --> 20:09.617
[Tad] lt'll take a few minutes for the spots
in your eyes to go away, but they will.

20:09.695 --> 20:12.687
- oK.
- We're right here.

20:15.034 --> 20:17.059
Is it always like that?

20:19.004 --> 20:23.031
Well, pretty much.

20:23.876 --> 20:26.401
- Shake-a-doo.
- Shake a what?

20:27.780 --> 20:29.907
It just means "Wow."

20:32.218 --> 20:35.676
Shake-a-doo.
Shake-a-doo, I like that.

20:35.755 --> 20:37.746
So...

20:39.191 --> 20:41.955
- You excited?
- Are you kidding?

20:42.027 --> 20:45.622
- This is like a fairy tale.
- Yeah, I figured.

20:50.336 --> 20:53.635
- You oK?
- Yeah.

20:53.706 --> 20:56.436
I'm just not used to sitting
sideways like this.

20:59.011 --> 21:02.105
We don't have sideways seating
in West Virginia.

21:02.181 --> 21:05.480
And I think the cigarette smoke
is kind of...

21:05.551 --> 21:08.577
You can come sit back here if you like.

21:09.155 --> 21:11.146
I can't really move right now.

21:12.124 --> 21:16.151
Boy, I don't feel well. I've always been
kind of motion sickness-y.

21:16.228 --> 21:18.788
once, this carnival
came to Fraziers Bottom,

21:18.864 --> 21:21.424
and they had that ride
where it spins around

21:21.500 --> 21:27.439
and you have to stand against the side
and the center falls out.

21:27.506 --> 21:30.134
- And I...
- Damn it.

21:32.111 --> 21:33.635
- Pardon me.

21:33.712 --> 21:35.179
Ahh!

21:38.984 --> 21:42.317
This is just so far from the way
I imagined the evening going.

21:45.291 --> 21:48.454
It's perfectly all right.
Right, Mickey?

21:48.527 --> 21:50.893
- Perfectly all right.
- [Tad] Shall we?

21:50.963 --> 21:54.228
[Mickey] Have a nice dinner.
I'll just be out here scrubbing.

21:54.300 --> 21:55.995
[Tad] Hey, Steve.

21:56.068 --> 21:59.162
- Good to see you, Mr. Hamilton.
- Good to see you, Larry.

21:59.238 --> 22:02.537
- Hey, man, how are you?
- What's up?

22:15.754 --> 22:17.654
Hey.

22:17.723 --> 22:19.714
This way.

22:23.963 --> 22:27.057
Doesn't it hurt,
smiling like that all the time?

22:28.834 --> 22:31.359
You get used to it.

22:31.437 --> 22:33.428
- Should I do it?
- Yeah.

22:33.505 --> 22:36.167
You might not be able
to hold it long, but go for it.

22:36.242 --> 22:38.233
Sure I will.

22:43.916 --> 22:47.215
See that?
It sort of gets you right there.

22:47.286 --> 22:50.722
- That's horrible.
- I told you.

22:52.057 --> 22:55.618
- You sure do have a lot of stuff.
- Yeah, sorry.

22:55.694 --> 22:58.663
I'm never out of touch
with the people who torment me.

22:58.731 --> 23:00.961
Who are they?

23:01.033 --> 23:04.434
Agents, managers, people like that.

23:04.503 --> 23:08.030
This man, Jimmy Ing, who's
making this movie I'm exactly right for

23:08.107 --> 23:11.008
but, for whatever reason,
he's taking a breath.

23:11.076 --> 23:14.341
- A what?
- He's thinking it over.

23:14.413 --> 23:18.713
It's just all very competitive,
this business, that's all.

23:18.784 --> 23:21.878
Everybody seems to be
chasing the same thing.

23:21.954 --> 23:26.288
The same parts in the same movies,
the same awards, the same big money.

23:27.326 --> 23:31.285
Well, I'm sure you have too much common
sense to get caught up in all that.

23:33.332 --> 23:36.995
I mean, it's just a recipe
for an unsatisfying life.

23:40.639 --> 23:43.472
obviously you have
your priorities straight, so...

23:45.110 --> 23:49.706
- So, Rosalee, what do you do?
- I work in a Piggly Wiggly.

23:49.782 --> 23:52.444
- I'm sorry?
- A supermarket.

23:52.518 --> 23:54.509
- I bag and check.
- Cool.

23:54.586 --> 23:56.645
Yeah. It's a real dream come true.

23:58.157 --> 24:01.126
But it's fun.
My two best friends work there.

24:05.030 --> 24:08.932
So, what do you do, Tad?

24:09.868 --> 24:12.166
Oops.

24:13.739 --> 24:19.439
What I mean is, what do you do
when you're not doing what you do?

24:19.511 --> 24:21.479
Not a lot, you know.

24:23.015 --> 24:26.610
There's not a lot of time
left for hobbies, really.

24:26.685 --> 24:31.281
And I don't really like watching sports,
so I read.

24:31.357 --> 24:35.851
Play with my dog,
my cat, my bird, you know.

24:36.862 --> 24:40.298
I... I love animals, you know?

24:45.170 --> 24:48.367
What do you think
they're doing right now?

24:48.440 --> 24:53.707
I bet they're in her hotel room,
straining for breath.

24:53.779 --> 24:56.907
His manhood yearning to be free.

24:56.982 --> 25:00.850
Her hands running over
the ripples in his abdomen.

25:00.919 --> 25:04.446
Her perfect bosom crying out in ecstasy.

25:08.994 --> 25:10.689
Great.

25:10.763 --> 25:12.754
All righty.

25:27.046 --> 25:30.243
- I had one of those.
- A retainer?

25:30.315 --> 25:34.081
Yeah, on the lowers
and a night brace for the uppers.

25:34.153 --> 25:36.144
I had really bad teeth as a kid.

25:36.221 --> 25:38.815
Yeah, I'm sure
you were a real ugly duckling.

25:38.891 --> 25:43.885
I was like anybody else.
A little gawky, unsure who I was.

25:43.962 --> 25:46.226
Combination skin.

25:47.366 --> 25:50.563
- Well, you came together nicely.
- Thank you.

25:52.638 --> 25:54.629
So did you.

25:58.544 --> 26:01.638
- Bon appétit!
- Umm-hmm!

26:19.798 --> 26:21.789
[Rosie] Thanks, Mickey.

26:27.039 --> 26:30.031
oh, wow. This is beautiful.

26:30.976 --> 26:34.377
These people sure leave
a lot of lights on.

26:34.446 --> 26:36.437
It's beautiful.

26:37.883 --> 26:39.874
It is.

26:42.054 --> 26:46.115
And you, if I may say so,
are also very beautiful.

26:50.329 --> 26:53.423
How would you like to come back
to my house for a little bit?

27:04.143 --> 27:06.805
Sure. For a little bit.

27:33.071 --> 27:37.735
- Shake-a-doo?
- No, shake-a-doo.

27:37.809 --> 27:39.800
Good.

27:45.017 --> 27:47.611
[Tad] Miss Ramirez.

27:47.686 --> 27:49.677
Sonja.

27:50.455 --> 27:52.047
Anybody in the casa?

27:58.297 --> 27:59.730
I think we're all alone.

28:00.999 --> 28:01.988
oh!

28:05.671 --> 28:08.663
Do you want to come in a little further?

28:11.710 --> 28:16.477
Um, you know what, Tad, thank you, but
I think I should get back to the hotel.

28:16.548 --> 28:17.879
Wow.

28:19.117 --> 28:20.448
oK.

28:21.553 --> 28:24.545
I don't want the concierge
to worry, you know.

28:25.791 --> 28:31.320
Good for you. Good for you.
I'll take you home.

28:31.396 --> 28:33.887
You don't have to do that.
You're already here.

28:33.966 --> 28:36.264
No, it would be my pleasure.

28:36.335 --> 28:39.668
oK, thanks.
That's really nice.

28:42.608 --> 28:45.839
Rosalee, it's been
wonderful to meet you.

28:45.911 --> 28:48.903
I wish you only good things in life.

28:49.982 --> 28:52.382
And to me, wonderfulness, too.

28:52.451 --> 28:56.444
And to you,
only the self same good wishes.

28:57.756 --> 29:00.657
- You know what I'm saying?
- Yeah, of course.

29:00.726 --> 29:04.321
- Thanks for the best night of my life.
- No, thank you.

