01:13:12.658 --> 01:13:14.888
And you're Tad Hamilton to me.

01:13:18.697 --> 01:13:20.927
Angelica, thank you.

01:13:21.000 --> 01:13:23.059
So start acting like it.

01:13:23.135 --> 01:13:25.330
oK.

01:13:26.839 --> 01:13:28.670
Yeah, oK.

01:13:30.209 --> 01:13:32.609
You are a really good bartender.

01:13:46.158 --> 01:13:47.989
- Hi.
- Hey.

01:13:48.060 --> 01:13:50.051
Come in, come in.

01:13:54.800 --> 01:13:56.791
I have something to talk to you about.

01:13:56.869 --> 01:13:58.860
- Me, too.
- Really? You go first.

01:13:58.938 --> 01:14:00.769
- No, you go first.
- No.

01:14:00.840 --> 01:14:04.105
- Seriously, you go first.
- oK.

01:14:04.176 --> 01:14:06.235
Tad got a part in this huge movie

01:14:06.312 --> 01:14:09.577
and he asked me to go with him
to California for the shoot.

01:14:09.648 --> 01:14:13.140
We leave tomorrow afternoon.
Isn't that great?

01:14:14.954 --> 01:14:16.819
I probably should've gone first.

01:14:16.889 --> 01:14:20.689
Why? What were you going to say?

01:14:22.461 --> 01:14:25.453
It's nothing. It was nothing.

01:14:25.531 --> 01:14:29.297
Just, you know, travel safely, oK?

01:14:29.368 --> 01:14:31.859
And just really enjoy the shoot.

01:14:36.475 --> 01:14:39.205
Actually, no, I remember
what I was going to say.

01:14:50.856 --> 01:14:52.847
I love you, Rosie.

01:14:54.193 --> 01:14:56.684
I always have.

01:14:56.762 --> 01:15:00.459
If I've been a jerk this last week,
it's because I have been fighting.

01:15:01.300 --> 01:15:03.495
I have been fighting for you.

01:15:05.104 --> 01:15:08.835
I don't want to lose you
to Tad Hamilton or anyone else.

01:15:13.679 --> 01:15:15.670
You're the one.

01:15:22.588 --> 01:15:26.115
So, any reaction to any of this?

01:15:26.191 --> 01:15:29.922
Because now would be an excellent time.

01:15:33.899 --> 01:15:37.391
Now? You kiss me now?

01:15:38.704 --> 01:15:43.937
You say this to me now,
after 22 years of being my friend?

01:15:46.111 --> 01:15:49.877
Yes, to all questions.

01:15:53.419 --> 01:15:55.410
I'm...

01:15:58.257 --> 01:16:00.248
I have to pack.

01:16:03.295 --> 01:16:05.695
You're telling me that you can't answer

01:16:05.764 --> 01:16:08.927
the most important question
I'll ever ask in my entire life

01:16:09.001 --> 01:16:11.367
because you have to pack?

01:16:11.437 --> 01:16:14.838
Not only do I have to pack, but I have
a load of whites in the dryer,

01:16:14.907 --> 01:16:18.070
and my dad called my relatives
from San Clemente

01:16:18.143 --> 01:16:20.475
and they're expecting me, so...

01:16:20.546 --> 01:16:22.537
it's all in the works.

01:16:22.614 --> 01:16:24.605
But this is...

01:16:26.385 --> 01:16:30.412
Rosie, what's in your heart?

01:16:39.732 --> 01:16:41.723
I'm sorry.

01:16:50.609 --> 01:16:52.600
I'm sorry, too.

01:17:08.727 --> 01:17:12.288
- You oK, Pete?
- Yes, sir.

01:17:12.364 --> 01:17:15.925
Listen, Pete, obviously
we've all been a little seduced

01:17:16.001 --> 01:17:18.367
by Tad Hamilton's presence.

01:17:20.205 --> 01:17:23.470
No one more so than me.

01:17:23.542 --> 01:17:28.172
But that doesn't mean I don't know
who cares about my daughter the most

01:17:28.247 --> 01:17:32.240
and who she would be with
if the world were fair.

01:17:35.921 --> 01:17:40.483
- Well, it's not.
- No. No, it's not.

01:17:41.927 --> 01:17:47.365
When I was your age I was completely
in love with Eleanor Hershey.

01:17:50.636 --> 01:17:54.197
of the chocolate Hersheys?

01:17:54.273 --> 01:17:57.504
The Hershey chocolates?

01:17:58.310 --> 01:18:00.938
She was a great girl,
completely unpretentious.

01:18:01.013 --> 01:18:03.948
I actually met her
filling her Cadillac up with gas.

01:18:05.217 --> 01:18:08.550
Anyway, there was this French guy.
He was really rich.

01:18:08.620 --> 01:18:12.317
He owned, like, France.

01:18:12.391 --> 01:18:14.689
I didn't stand a chance.

01:18:14.760 --> 01:18:17.888
It happens that way sometimes.
It shouldn't, but it does.

01:18:17.963 --> 01:18:22.127
Sometimes Goliath
kicks the shit out of David.

01:18:23.135 --> 01:18:26.195
It's just nobody bothers
to tell that story.

01:18:27.840 --> 01:18:30.331
Well, thanks, Mr. Futch.

01:18:31.743 --> 01:18:34.143
I feel much better now.

01:18:37.883 --> 01:18:41.910
- Goodbye, Mr. Futch.
- Take it easy, Pete.

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:01.594
Are you sure you know what you're doing?

01:19:01.669 --> 01:19:03.330
No.

01:19:03.404 --> 01:19:06.464
Ever feel more confused or alone?

01:19:06.541 --> 01:19:08.532
No.

01:19:08.610 --> 01:19:10.771
Have a nice flight.

01:19:35.522 --> 01:19:38.355
[Mr. Futch] So, we'll see you
after principal photography.

01:19:22.557 --> 01:19:25.185
Yes, Daddy.

01:19:25.260 --> 01:19:28.718
You guys don't mind not flying with us?
We need our privacy.

01:19:28.796 --> 01:19:30.787
- That's fine.
- Yeah.

01:19:30.865 --> 01:19:33.800
We look forward
to our shit-ass commercial flight.

01:19:33.868 --> 01:19:36.393
I always wanted
a layover in Cincinnati.

01:19:36.471 --> 01:19:39.031
- We will be absolutely fine.
- Another one in Chicago.

01:19:39.107 --> 01:19:41.098
So we'll be in LA by April?

01:19:44.546 --> 01:19:46.878
We'll be fine.

01:19:47.882 --> 01:19:50.112
- It's time.
- oK.

01:19:50.184 --> 01:19:53.244
- Safe trip, Tad.
- Bye, honey.

01:19:56.925 --> 01:20:00.258
- Welcome aboard, Mr. Hamilton.
- Bye.

01:20:00.328 --> 01:20:02.660
- Miss?
- Thank you.

01:20:07.402 --> 01:20:10.803
Stop it. Stop it.
What's the matter with you?

01:20:10.872 --> 01:20:14.239
Come on.
Commercial isn't so bad.

01:20:14.309 --> 01:20:16.641
There's got to be room for one more.

01:20:16.711 --> 01:20:19.111
Will you pull yourself together?

01:20:19.180 --> 01:20:21.171
Thank you.

01:20:21.249 --> 01:20:23.080
Would you like a Vicodin?

01:21:04.859 --> 01:21:08.022
[Tad] Jimmy, being
in your movie is a privilege.

01:21:08.096 --> 01:21:12.692
In fact, it's more than a privilege.
It's a real privilege.

01:21:14.135 --> 01:21:17.366
Can I... Do you mind if I call you back
in a few minutes?

01:21:18.906 --> 01:21:21.238
oK, thank you, sir.

01:21:33.388 --> 01:21:35.720
- You oK?
- Mm-hmm.

01:21:37.291 --> 01:21:39.987
I'm just a little nervous
for some reason.

01:21:41.396 --> 01:21:44.058
I have a little nervous feeling
in my... self.

01:21:45.433 --> 01:21:47.924
- But that's only natural, right?
- Yeah.

01:21:48.002 --> 01:21:50.835
This is a pretty huge thing I'm doing.

01:21:50.905 --> 01:21:53.339
Kind of a great leap of faith.

01:21:53.408 --> 01:21:56.400
But I have that faith in you.

01:21:57.612 --> 01:22:00.672
So I'm fine. It's going to be great.

01:22:00.748 --> 01:22:04.775
- Good.
- Can't you tell by my smile?

01:22:08.823 --> 01:22:11.314
Which one is it?

01:22:12.293 --> 01:22:15.160
- What?
- What number smile is it?

01:22:15.229 --> 01:22:17.254
It's...

01:22:17.331 --> 01:22:20.391
Wait, it was one.

01:22:24.105 --> 01:22:27.700
No, one was when something
really made me laugh.

01:22:28.843 --> 01:22:32.074
- Right?
- one and a half.

01:22:49.297 --> 01:22:51.527
Rosie...

01:22:53.134 --> 01:22:56.934
I didn't know about your six smiles.
Pete told me about them.

01:22:57.004 --> 01:22:59.734
He made me swear
I wasn't going to break your heart,

01:22:59.807 --> 01:23:01.798
or he would tear me to pieces,

01:23:01.876 --> 01:23:06.245
either with his bare hands
or his rhetoric.

01:23:07.582 --> 01:23:10.710
I stole the speech from Pete
to get you to come here with me.

01:23:10.785 --> 01:23:13.549
I lied. And I'm sorry.

01:23:15.623 --> 01:23:18.285
And I know you're going to be
very upset. I just...

01:23:20.762 --> 01:23:24.391
- Pete told you about the six smiles?
- Yeah.

01:23:24.465 --> 01:23:28.492
And made you swear
that you wouldn't break my heart?

01:23:28.569 --> 01:23:33.438
or he'd tear you to pieces, with either
his bare hands or his rhetoric?

01:23:33.508 --> 01:23:35.066
Yeah.

01:23:37.678 --> 01:23:40.841
That is just so...

01:23:44.519 --> 01:23:46.510
adorable.

01:23:49.690 --> 01:23:51.817
What?

01:23:52.627 --> 01:23:55.596
Do you think it's possible

01:23:55.663 --> 01:24:00.327
to love someone your whole life
and never really realize it

01:24:00.401 --> 01:24:04.770
until something happens
that makes you see?

01:24:05.740 --> 01:24:08.971
- What's that from?
- No, it's not from anything.

01:24:09.043 --> 01:24:11.603
I'm just saying it to you.

01:24:15.416 --> 01:24:17.714
Wow.

01:24:27.695 --> 01:24:30.186
Man, what a week.

01:24:31.933 --> 01:24:36.427
Fell in love for the first time,
got my heart broken for the first time,

01:24:36.504 --> 01:24:39.405
was honorable for the first time.

01:24:39.473 --> 01:24:43.204
Got bit in the ass for being
honorable for the first time.

01:24:43.277 --> 01:24:45.609
Bought a farm.

01:24:45.680 --> 01:24:48.376
I'm sorry about the broken-heart part.

01:24:59.026 --> 01:25:02.018
Do you think
you could take me home now?

01:25:03.931 --> 01:25:06.297
Yeah.

01:25:18.713 --> 01:25:20.704
Thank you.

01:25:23.251 --> 01:25:25.481
- Cathy.
- Rosie?

01:25:25.553 --> 01:25:28.681
- Where's Pete?
- He's not here. What are you doing?

01:25:28.756 --> 01:25:31.224
What do you mean?
He's always here. He's Pete.

01:25:31.292 --> 01:25:33.783
No. He didn't come in today.

01:25:35.863 --> 01:25:38.661
Can I borrow your car?

01:25:38.733 --> 01:25:41.099
Yes.

01:25:41.836 --> 01:25:43.827
Thank you.

01:25:56.584 --> 01:25:58.575
Pete. Pete.

01:26:07.662 --> 01:26:09.653
Not Pete.

01:26:12.466 --> 01:26:14.457
Wow.

01:26:28.783 --> 01:26:31.775
I'm just here because Pete
asked me to box up some stuff.

01:26:33.621 --> 01:26:36.146
- Why? Where's he going?
- Richmond.

01:26:37.425 --> 01:26:39.655
And he isn't going.

01:26:39.727 --> 01:26:41.718
He's gone.

01:26:42.897 --> 01:26:45.127
He's gone to Richmond?

01:26:45.199 --> 01:26:47.190
Why?

01:26:48.736 --> 01:26:52.331
I cannot believe I am taking
my work home with me.

01:26:56.310 --> 01:27:01.771
When great love is rejected, Rosalee,
something inside a man dies.

01:27:02.817 --> 01:27:04.808
So all he can do is run away,

01:27:04.885 --> 01:27:08.844
where he can meet the girl
he'll love second most.

01:27:12.660 --> 01:27:15.060
- Unless...
- Unless what?

01:27:15.129 --> 01:27:18.155
Unless you can get to him
before he closes the book on you.

01:27:20.601 --> 01:27:23.934
But once it's closed, it's closed.

01:27:24.005 --> 01:27:27.031
It's finished. It's gone, dead.

01:27:27.108 --> 01:27:30.339
It's crushed. It's beaten. It's buried.

01:27:30.411 --> 01:27:32.641
It is lost for all of time in a sea...

01:27:32.713 --> 01:27:36.149
- Angelica.
- oK, yeah.

01:27:37.184 --> 01:27:39.175
I owe you.

01:27:41.922 --> 01:27:43.913
Go.

01:28:12.386 --> 01:28:15.753
[announcer] If you've been dumped,
give us a call on late-night talk.

01:28:15.823 --> 01:28:18.018
Let's go to line one.
Scott, you're on...

01:28:30.004 --> 01:28:32.564
What? Pass me.

01:28:34.942 --> 01:28:37.433
Pete. Pete.

01:28:50.658 --> 01:28:54.025
- Are you oK?
- Yeah. No...

01:28:54.095 --> 01:28:56.086
No, I meant to do that.

01:29:28.696 --> 01:29:31.164
You have five smiles, Pete.

01:29:33.934 --> 01:29:37.563
one when you think someone's an idiot.

01:29:37.638 --> 01:29:40.630
one when you think
someone's really an idiot.

01:29:42.877 --> 01:29:47.075
one when you're getting all dressed up.

01:29:47.148 --> 01:29:49.309
one when you're singing Barry White.

01:29:51.218 --> 01:29:53.209
And one...

01:29:54.922 --> 01:29:56.947
when you're looking at me.

01:30:15.943 --> 01:30:19.504
[radio] For all you lovers out there,
this one's for you.

01:30:31.458 --> 01:30:34.552
I can't believe
I'm going to say this, but...

01:30:37.464 --> 01:30:39.455
would you like to dance?

